      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2 bgcolor='black' class='header'>ITEM COMMENTS</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2><b><font color='#80000'>HERO QUEST</font>, By Ratha</b><br><br><p>&nbsp;This is actually one of the easiest, albeit boring, quests in the game. Head to
Steamfont and the mino cave behind the windmills. In the mino caves there are some low
level mobs called slavers. The only one I really worry about is the first slaver at the cave entrance. He seems to be the trigger to get the Hero to come 'protect his people.' You can, if you have more than one person, kill other slavers in the cave to see if this helps get the hero to spawn, but if by yourself, don't worry much about it and save mana for the hero, he WILL spawn if you only kill first slaver.</p>
<p>&nbsp;The hero is a pretty random spawn, but the trigger slaver at the entrance spawns every 6 min 30 sec, so you can go watch TV between spawns. ;-) When the hero does spawn, he'll be across the valley from the tunnel entrance near the tree on the opposite hill. After he spawns, he will walk around behind the giant gears following the ridge line and around to the tunnel entrance. When he reaches it he will de-spawn. Just jump him before that, kill him and snag the mino hero bracer.&nbsp;</p>
<p> Run over to Qeynos and in the bottom of the arena is a guy who's name is something like
Graham D-(something here). Ask him about the second escaped gladiator and if your faction is high enough (mid to high amiable) he'll tell you about the mino hero and tell you to return the shackles. Fork them over and the bracers are yours. On a side note, turning in bags of DF Belts to Cain Darkmoore in FP will also raise faction fairly quickly. The hero himself is about 35 and just a tank, so no problem if you can kite or just plain out
level him. Good luck  =)</p>
<br><hr size='1'></td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2><b><font color='#80000'>FACTION</font>, By Legonaire</b><br><br><p>&nbsp;OK Well the easiest part of this quest is actually getting the Hero Shackles. The long tedious part of this quest is trying to get the faction if you are not a Human Warrior who starts in Qeynos. Myself, I am a Wood Elf Ranger, I started this quest as apprehensive to the Steel Warriors. I turned in close to 200 Gnoll fangs to the warrior guild in Halas, I returned to Qeynos to find that I was now indifferent to the Steel Warriors. I decided that I would try the Deatfist Slashed belt quest in Freeport to obtain faction ( besides you can buy the belts, gnoll fangs are no drop ). I bought probably close to 100 belts. For every 10 belts I turned into the warrior guild in Freeport I would turn in 2 to the Militia as well. I am now indifferent in all of Freeport, but amiable still in North Freeport and to the Warrior guild. I returned to Qeynos to find myself now amiable to
there Steel Warriors but still not of high enough faction to do the quest. being amiable I decided to do the warrior initiation quest, upon completing this quest I was now high enough amiable to finally finish the Hero Bracer quest...<br>
<br>
All in all I think I spent close to 400pp and 3 straight days trying to increase faction. I believe it is worth it because I now have the satisfaction of completing the quest, and if I should see fit I can do it again and again and again.. hope this information helps !!<br>
<br>
Legonaire Ranger of Morell-Thule</p>
<br><hr size='1'></td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2><b><font color='#80000'>FACTION FOR STEEL WARRIOR</font>, By Waza zaabi</b><br><br><p>&nbsp;I just turn 160 gnoll teethes to the pit of doom in hales to get sufficient faction to get the quest.
Btw gnoll teethes should be given three at a time.<br>
Hope that helps.<br>
</p>
<br><hr size='1'></td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2><b><font color='#80000'>HERO BRACER</font>, By Egaal of veeshan</b><br><br>Ok, the hero mino spawns in Steamfont mts. Kill him and get his shackle.  Take the shackle to Qeynos, down inside the arena there is a guy, the guy that gives the escaped catman quest.  Ask him about the second escaped gladiator.  If you don't have high enough faction he will tell you.  To get better faction get gnoll fangs in Blackburrow, and turn them into the female npc in halas arena.  I have heard it takes about 150-200 if you are indif to start.  You can also kill dorn and D'vinn and get good faction with the steel Warriors.  <br><hr size='1'></td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2><b><font color='#80000'>WRONG INFO</font>, By Shadowreaper</b><br><br>The Hero Bracer is only wearble by medium races now.<br><hr size='1'></td>
